		}]
	}, {
		id: "000000000000A033"
		x: 8.0d
		y: -2.0d
		dependencies: ["000000000000A02F"]
		title: "Soul Forged Metal"
		icon: {id: "soulland:soul_forged_ingot", Count: 1b}
		description: ["Soul Forged Ingots are the Soul Land equivalent of steel — and now they require actual steel to make. Craft them from Spirit Iron, Qi Crystal, and Stainless Steel Ingots from GregTech. Qi Crystal Ore spawns closer to diamond depth.", "Stainless Steel comes from the Electric Blast Furnace — you need MV infrastructure and chromite or nickel to produce it. This ingot is the bridge between GregTech HV tier and Soul Land mid-tier armor. Get two to prove the process works, then stockpile for the full set."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "000000000000A034"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "soulland:soul_forged_ingot", Count: 1b}
			count: 2L
		}]
		rewards: [{
			id: "000000000000A035"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "soulland:qi_crystal", Count: 2b}
		}]
	}, {
		id: "000000000000A036"
		x: 10.0d
		y: -2.0d
		dependencies: ["000000000000A033"]
		title: "Soul Forged Armor"
		icon: {id: "soulland:soul_forged_chestplate", Count: 1b}
		description: ["The Soul Forged set. Craft all four pieces at the Forging Table. Apply M&S Stat Souls to each piece immediately after crafting.", "Soul Forged Chestplate is now the crafting base for mid-tier M&S armor stat souls at the Gear Crafting Station — replace the vanilla iron_boots requirement entirely. Soul Forged Ingot replaces the mining material. This is the tier 3 window: the souls you craft here will carry you into Act IV.", "This armor is fully compatible with Apotheosis gems socketed via the M&S Socket Orb — four pieces, four potential sockets, four gems stacking on top of your affixes and stat souls. Don't skip the sockets."]
		tasks: [{
